Mr. John A. Shapiro serves as the President at Morgan Stanley Capital Group Inc. Mr. Shapiro served as Global Head of Commodities at Morgan Stanley & Co., until July 2008, where he had served for more than 24 years in various capacities. Prior to joining Morgan Stanley & Co., he worked for Conoco, Inc. and New England Merchants National Bank. Mr. Shapiro has been a Director of Blue Wolf Mongolia Holdings Corp. since April 2011. Mr. Shapiro has been a Director of Blueknight Energy Partners G.P., LLC of Blueknight Energy Partners, L.P. since November 2009. He serves as a Director of Heidmar Inc. In addition, he serves on the board of directors of Citymeals-on-Wheels. He served as Director of TransMontaigne Inc. Mr. Shapiro has been a lecturer at Princeton University, Harvard University School of Government, HEC Business School (Paris, France) and Oxford University Energy Program (Oxford, UK). He holds an MBA from Harvard University and a Bachelors degree in Economics from Princeton University.



